0.1.9: the wizard's Kind-guessing heuristic (and the pre-existing server/dashboard copies it mirrored) assumed any `api.deepseek.com` URL wanted kind=deepseek, and printed active guidance telling operators a base URL ending in `/anthropic` was wrong for a non-anthropic kind — but some vendors (DeepSeek confirmed) expose a real, documented Anthropic-protocol-compatible path of their own (`https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic`), for which kind=anthropic is correct. This actively steered operators away from a legitimate, working setup. Bare-metal's missing dashboard-standalone relocation (see 0.1.2) is also still present here. Kind-guessing fixed in 0.1.10, dashboard relocation fixed in 0.1.12. PLUS the PreToolUse hook script was missing from the minimal Docker image / bare-metal's hook path never matched either (see 0.1.0). Fixed in 0.1.14.
0.1.10: infra/setup-wizard.mjs's masked-input prompt (used for every secret/token field) called `rl.question('', cb)` plus a manual redraw on each keystroke to fake password masking — but readline's own internal line-refresh runs even with an empty prompt string, wiping the just-printed field label right after it appears; it then only reappears once the first keystroke triggers the manual redraw. Visually this looks like "the field doesn't appear until you start typing" — a real, reproducible bug present since the wizard was first shipped (0.1.1). Bare-metal's missing dashboard-standalone relocation (see 0.1.2) is also still present here. Masked-input bug fixed in 0.1.11, dashboard relocation fixed in 0.1.12. PLUS the PreToolUse hook script was missing from the minimal Docker image / bare-metal's hook path never matched either (see 0.1.0). Fixed in 0.1.14.
